annotationA: Putative ATP-dependent RNA helicase me31b; Unwinds RNA in an ATP-dependent fashion (Potential). Involved in germ cell formation
annotationB: Twin, isoform C; Protein binding. It is involved in the biological process described with: mRNA catabolic process; oogenesis; nuclear-transcribed mRNA catabolic process, deadenylation-dependent decay; regulation of transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter; female germ-line stem cell asymmetric division; nuclear-transcribed mRNA poly(A) tail shortening; negative regulation of translation
